    <entry name="AstraMilitarum/GulagGains" value="Sentence Delivered"/>
    <!-- <entry name="AstraMilitarum/GulagGainsDescription" value=""/> -->
    <entry name="AstraMilitarum/GulagGainsFlavor" value="Forced labour, while not the most efficient, is overall quite effective when you have a limitless supply of prisoners. Typically, prisoners are sent into dangerous mines, with freedom promised if they can deliver enough ore by the end of the month. Unofficially, backstabbing is overlooked since it helps control the constantly growing traitor population. Anyone who meets these bounties is collected and placed into a soundproof voidship, where they are granted the Emperor's Peace."/>
    <!--    Commander-->
    <entry name="HoldTheLine" value="<string name='Actions/AstraMilitarum/HoldTheLine'/>"/>
    <entry name="HoldTheLineDescription" value="Infantry which have not moved take less damage; Valhallans also gain increased melee attacks. Infantry within 5 tiles of an allied city have improved defences and damage. Valhallans within 3 tiles of an allied city have an increased healing rate."/>
    <entry name="HoldTheLineFlavor" value="<string name='Actions/AstraMilitarum/HoldTheLineFlavor'/>"/>
    <entry name="ThePeoplesCommissar" value="<string name='Actions/AstraMilitarum/ThePeoplesCommissar'/>"/>
    <entry name="ThePeoplesCommissarDescription" value="Infantry have less upkeep and restore morale each turn. Valhallans gain melee attacks."/>
    <entry name="ThePeoplesCommissarFlavor" value="Valhallans adore their drinks. Naturally you'll find the usual suspects, alcohol and recaf, but there's one exotic choice: tanna. A leafy plant native to Valhalla, it is often brewed into a tea with a pungent aftertaste. Few offworlders can stomach it; Valhallans crave it."/>
    <entry name="AstraMilitarum/StrongpointReinforced" value="Reinforced Strongpoint"/>
    <entry name="AstraMilitarum/StrongpointReinforcedDescription" value="The Fortification (excluding Headquarters) gain increased offensive capabilities. When adjacent to 3 allies, it takes less damage."/>
    <entry name="AstraMilitarum/StrongpointReinforcedFlavor" value="<string name='Actions/AstraMilitarum/DefendThisStrongpointFlavor'/>"/>
    <entry name="TheMotherlandCalls" value="<string name='Actions/AstraMilitarum/TheMotherlandCalls'/>"/>
    <entry name="TheMotherlandCallsDescription" value=" Infantry gains damage reduction, moresof if they are Valhallans. If within 5 tiles of an allied Headquarters, infantry gain an additional action."/>
    <entry name="TheMotherlandCallsFlavor" value="<string name='Actions/AstraMilitarum/TheMotherlandCallsFlavor'/>"/>
    <!--    Night Witches-->
    <entry name="AstraMilitarum/NightBomber" value="<string name='Actions/AstraMilitarum/NightBomber'/>"/>
    <entry name="AstraMilitarum/NightBomberDescription" value="Unit gains damage reduction, increased damage against Headquarters, and even more damage against Fortifications (excluding Headquarters)."/>
    <entry name="AstraMilitarum/NightBomberFlavor" value="Undetected, unexpected, bombers slip past enemy defences under the cover of night. Troopers are shaken awake by crashing structures and explosions, only to find their bunkers and turret nests in smoldering ruins. By this handiwork, they know they have been struck by the 588th Night Bombers."/>
    <entry name="AstraMilitarum/FlyLow" value="<string name='Actions/AstraMilitarum/FlyLow'/>"/>
    <entry name="AstraMilitarum/FlyLowDescription" value="Gains accuracy but takes more damage."/>
    <entry name="AstraMilitarum/FlyLowFlavor" value="<string name='Actions/AstraMilitarum/FlyLowFlavor'/>"/>
    <entry name="AstraMilitarum/FlyLowSlowdown" value="<string name='Actions/AstraMilitarum/FlyLow'/> Slowdown"/>
    <entry name="AstraMilitarum/FlyLowSlowdownDescription" value="Reduces movement. Removed after levelling up the action."/>
    <entry name="AstraMilitarum/FlyLowSlowdownFlavor" value="<string name='Actions/AstraMilitarum/FlyLowFlavor'/>"/>
    <entry name="WitchHarassment" value="Harassed"/>
    <entry name="WitchHarassmentDescription" value="Accuracy is decreased and morale is lost every turn."/>
    <entry name="WitchHarassmentFlavor" value="Being awoken by bullets and bolt shells tearing apart the men in the next cot changes a man. Vigilence must be maintained through the night, reducing rest and therefore combat effectiveness for the next day."/>
    <entry name="AstraMilitarum/LoadExtraAmmo" value="<string name='Actions/AstraMilitarum/LoadExtraAmmo'/>"/>
    <entry name="AstraMilitarum/LoadExtraAmmoDescription" value="Greatly improves offence. Heavy Bomb Clusters are refilled."/>
    <entry name="AstraMilitarum/LoadExtraAmmoFlavor" value="<string name='Actions/AstraMilitarum/LoadExtraAmmoFlavor'/>"/>
    <!-- For Weapons -->
    <entry name="ValhallanHotWeapon" value="Hot Weapon"/>
    <entry name="ValhallanHotWeaponDescription" value="Wielder takes damage when firing while on tiles which are neither Arctic nor Tundra tiles. When on Desert, Savannah, or Volcanic tiles, take even more damage."/>
    <entry name="ValhallanHotWeaponFlavor" value="In cold environments, weapons can cool down quicker, and natives of those lands typically modify their weapons to take advantage of this. Of course, this may backfire when they're deployed to environments outside of their preferred."/>
    <entry name="AstraMilitarum/ValhallanTankHunters" value="<string name='Traits/AstraMilitarum/Valhallan'/> <string name='Traits/TankHunters'/>"/>
    <entry name="AstraMilitarum/ValhallanTankHuntersDescription" value="<string name='Traits/TankHuntersDescription'/> Decreased accuracy against Infantry."/>
    <entry name="AstraMilitarum/ValhallanTankHuntersFlavor" value="<string name='Traits/TankHuntersFlavor'/>"/>
    <entry name="ValhallanUnwieldy" value="Indirect Fire Inaccuracy"/>
    <entry name="ValhallanUnwieldyDescription" value="Decreased accuracy against units that are not Fortifications."/>
    <entry name="ValhallanUnwieldyFlavor" value="Hitting a moving target is hard enough. Hitting a moving target by predicting its path of travel and intercepting that with a calculated direct hit from a mortar shell is much harder."/>
    <entry name="TripodSetup" value="Requires Tripod"/>
    <entry name="TripodSetupDescription" value="When wielded by infantry, this weapon cannot be fired immediately after moving."/>
    <entry name="TripodSetupFlavor" value="Many weapons are meant to be mounted on vehicles, but stubborn infantrymen find a way to make it work. Will the results be cumbersome and painful? Yes. Will that stop them? No."/>
